<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Bootstrap Responsive Page</title>

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
</head>
<body>

<div class="container mt-4">

    <h1 class="text-center">Student Details</h1>

    <div class="row mt-4">

        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h3>Name</h3>
                    <p>Arafat Momin</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6 mt-3 mt-md-0">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h3>City</h3>
                    <p>Sangli</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

    <button class="btn btn-primary mt-4">Submit</button>

</div>

</body>
</html>
 
Code explanation
Bootstrap CSS link
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
This loads Bootstrap, so you can use ready-made responsive classes.
Container
<div class="container">
container gives proper spacing from page edges.
Row
<div class="row">
A row is used to hold columns.
Columns
<div class="col-md-6">
This uses Bootstrap Grid.
•	On medium and larger screens, each column takes 6 parts out of 12, so two columns appear side by side. 
•	On small screens, they automatically come one below another. 
That is why the page is responsive.
Card
<div class="card">
card is a Bootstrap component used to show content inside a box.
Button
<button class="btn btn-primary">
Creates a Bootstrap styled button.
